# inner-space.px — The Inner Space (v3 Dataflow)
#
# The inner-space is the virtual world / mental landscape.
# Wind-chess is ONE game that can run INSIDE the inner-space.
# Inner-space manages spatial environments: rooms, ambient effects,
# entities (NPCs), and the rendering pipeline that composites
# game frames into the larger world view.
#
# Queue topology:
#
#   frame_output (from wind-chess) ──────────────────────────────────────┐
#                                                                        ▼
#   spatial_command ─→ [process_command] ─→ world_state ─→ [compose_scene]
#                                              ↑                    │
#                                              │                    ▼
#   ambient_clock ─→ [tick_ambience] ──────────┘           [render_world] ─→ world_frame
#                                                                   ↑
#   npc_input ─→ [npc_behavior] ─→ entity_update ──────────────────┘
#

import games::wind_chess

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Entity Schemas
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

